05922nam a22009015i 9781501501326DE-B159720180522022738.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||180522s2018    gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97815015013267 a10.1515/97815015013262doi  a(DE-B1597)444410  a(OCoLC)1037980507  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aP120.L34bL35 2018 7aLAN0090002bisacsh 7aLAN0090502bisacsh04a401.922300aLanguage Awareness in Multilingual Classrooms in Europe :bFrom Theory to Practice /ced. by Christine Hélot, Carolien Frijns, Koen Gorp, Sven Sierens. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2018] 4c©2018  a1 online resource (317 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aContributions to the Sociology of Language [CSL] ;v10900tFrontmatter -- tForeword / rCummins, Jim -- tContents -- tIntroduction: Towards Critical Multilingual Language Awareness for 21st century schools / rHélot, Christine / Gorp, Koen Van / Frijns, Carolien / Sierens, Sven -- tThe effects of raising language awareness in mainstream and language classrooms: A literature review (1995-2013) / rSierens, Sven / Frijns, Carolien / Gorp, Koen Van / Sercu, Lies / Avermaet, Piet Van -- tServing policy or people? Towards an evidence-based, coherent concept of language awareness for all learners / rFrijns, Carolien / Sierens, Sven / Avermaet, Piet Van / Sercu, Lies / Gorp, Koen Van -- tA critical approach to language awareness in France: Learning to live with Babel / rHélot, Christine -- tLanguage awareness amongst "new speakers" in a multilingual classroom / rBermingham, Nicola / O'Rourke, Bernadette -- tFrom plurilingual repertoires to language awareness: Developing primary pupils' proficiency in the language of schooling / rLittle, David / Kirwan, Déirdre -- tBuilding students' language awareness and literacy engagement through the creation of collaborative multilingual identity texts 2.0 / rPrasad, Gail -- tLanguage awareness in action: Primary school students' language practices while performing a multilingual task / rGorp, Koen Van / Verheyen, Steven -- tBlack-blanc-beur: Challenges and opportunities for developing language awareness in teacher education in France / rMary, Latisha / Young, Andrea S. -- tIndex  aWithin the scope of today's globalisation, linguistic diversity is a given fact of the world we live in. In several educational contexts in Europe, language awareness (LA) activities have been introduced with the objective to prepare pupils cognitively, socially and/or critically for life as multilingual, open minded and/or empowered citizens in a diverse world. Despite previous research in various contexts, the concept of LA remains problematic: a generally accepted, evidence-based conceptualisation is missing. This confronts both research and education with a challenge: in order to develop LA activities, implement them successfully in educational contexts and achieve the expected outcomes, we should know what the concept stands for, how it works and why we would choose to implement it in classrooms (or not). This volume focuses on three apparent simple questions: what, how and why? The first question - what? - refers to the concept(ual mess) of LA. The second question - how? - refers to the implementation of LA activities in several educational contexts. The third question - why? - is a recurrent theme running through all the chapters and deals with a reflection on the way we deal (un)consciously with LA activities in education.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Mai 2018) 0aLanguage awarenesszEurope. 0aLanguage awareness. 4aLanguage Awareness. 4aLanguage Education. 4aMehrsprachigkeit. 4aMultilingual Literacy. 4aMultilingualism. 4aSoziolinguistik.1 aFrijns, Carolien, eeditor.1 aGorp, Koen, eeditor.1 aHélot, Christine, eedito